@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About // System Specification</PageTitle>

<header class="max-w-5xl mx-auto mb-8 border-b border-[var(--border-subtle)] pb-4">
    <span class="text-cyber-metadata">SYS_SPEC // SYSTEM INFO</span>
    <h1 class="text-cyber-display mt-1 uppercase">About this system</h1>
</header>

<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-cyber-body space-y-4 leading-relaxed">
    <p>
        LAYLA is a high-precision collaborative writing environment. Operations allow 
        real-time novel co-authoring, technical worldbuilding wikis, and structured 
        narrative visualization graphs.
    </p>
    <p>
        This web client serves as a public operational interface — operating alongside a 
        high-fidelity WPF desktop application (the primary authoring workspace) and a 
        mobile helper. Each client establishes secure RPC links to a distributed backend: 
        an ASP.NET Core API for user identities and projects, and a worldbuilding engine 
        integrated with Neo4j and MongoDB.
    </p>
    <div class="pt-4 border-t border-[var(--border-subtle)] flex justify-between items-center text-cyber-metadata">
        <span>CORE VER // 1.0.0</span>
        <span class="text-[var(--accent-primary)]">SYS_ONLINE</span>
    </div>
</div>
